      • getDimensions

        org.bukkit.util.Vector getDimensions(java.io.File file,
                                     org.bukkit.Location to)
        Gets the dimensions of a structure file
        Parameters:
        file - The file
        to - A location (which is somehow required to determine the sizes). It is recommended you put the coords of where you want to paste this structure.
        Returns:
        the 3D dimensions (all positive)

      • setWorldBorder

        void setWorldBorder(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                    org.bukkit.util.Vector vector,
                    double size)
        Sets the world border for a player using NMS packets.
        Parameters:
        player - The player
        vector - The x and z value of this vector will be used to determine the center of the world border, so (100, 50, 100) will put the center of the world border at (100, 100)
        size - The length of one of the sizes of the world border (the playable area will be size/2 in all directions)
